<br>
::Spirits, the Dead, and Undead suddenly began gathering watching with a combination of fear and curiosity.  In almost a blink of an eye the two of them had appeared in the middle of Tartarus itself, instead of merely just the throne room::<br>
<br>
::The two combatants began fighting it out.  Not a single one of them could seem to best the other.  Their fighting styles almost mirrored one another.  Pluto, having the unrelenting fighting style of a Roman centurion, while Hades had the indominable fighting style of a Spartan warrior mixed in with the grace of an Athenian warrior.  The both of them seemed to fight for hours on end...time unknown had passed.  It felt like hours...maybe days...though in actuality it was only mere minutes.  With Nike 'on strike' no victor would be determined::<br>
<br>
::Finally frustrated Pluto takes a step back and calls out in anger to the gathered Dead:: &quot;Attack him!&quot;  ::Pointing right at the Spartan-like Hades::<br>
<br>
::Hades merely smirked as all gathered merely stood there confused.  Pluto himself seemed confused as to why they didn't attack::<br>
<br>
::Hades finally spoke::  &quot;You forgot one thing, Here...it is I who has home-field advantage.  You may be the Lord of the Dead where you come from...but here It is I who rules!&quot;  <br>
<br>
::A look of despair strikes Pluto for a brief moment as Hades looks around to all the gathered souls and says:: &quot;Will someone please show this poor Fool the way out of here?&quot;  <br>
<br>
::And with that, the entire horde of gathered souls converged upon Pluto, included in the onslaught was Cerberus, Thanatos, and Hades himself.  Before he knew it, Pluto found himself chained and shackled.  Hades then nodded to Thanatos and Cerberus to lead Pluto out of here and to take him back to the rift he came from.  Hades followed behind the procession marching like coming from a victorious battle even though it took only a point of a finger to beat him::<br>
<br>
:<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :O --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":O"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> nce the edge of Tartarus was reached, Hades took Pluto's chains and marched him topside.  Thanatos and Cerberus stayed behind.  Hades walked Pluto back to the opened red rift where Hypnos and company were::<br>
<br>
::Hades grabbed Pluto by the back of his head and spoke to him quietly:: &quot;You really should not be attacking me...we in actuality should be working together.  Perhaps one day when you learn your lessons, we will be allies and not foes.  But until that day.  STAY IN  YOUR OWN REALM.  You will not defeat me in my Underworld nor Olympus.  Just as I know I would not be able to defeat you in your home realm.&quot;<br>
<br>
::And with that Hades threw Pluto back into the red rift.  The then tured and faced the rest of the gods present, decked out in his Spartan uniform::  &quot;Anyone need a hand with anything while I'm here?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/24/01 8:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cat fight</span><hr size=1> ::Aphrodite's rage built inside of her.  It was obvious that Venus felt the same.  Both beauties stared each other down; their eyes full of rage.  The tense silence that surrounded them broke as Venus let out a piercing cry and lunged towards her Greek counterpart.  Instantly, Aphrodite met Venus' attack and leaped towards her.::  <br>
<br>
       ::The two immortals rolled on the ground tearing at each other hair and clothes.  Aphrodite picked up Venus and tossed her into a mud pit.::  &quot;Here ya go, little piggie.  Have a romp in your new home.&quot;<br>
<br>
        ::Venus was stunned at first but then she quickly got over it.  She grabbed Aphrodite's left leg and dragged her down into the mudpit::  &quot;It takes one to know one!&quot;<br>
<br>
      ::The two goddess continued their battle, splashing about.  Both immortals were covered in thick mud which hid their identies.  Literally, the two looked identical.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/25/01 12:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cat fight</span><hr size=1> ::Hades blinked for a moment as he saw Aphrodite and Venus suddenly begin fighting in front of him, then with the starting of the mudfighting he simply just stood at the edge of the mudpit and watched.  A smile crossed his face::<br>
<br>
&quot;My timing is immaculate as per usual.  Some places charge you to see action such as this.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades stood there watching the both of them, cheering 'Dite on::<br>
